<subSubSection id="FC8E653B875DB1061E0F5A21FBF8FDD4" lastPageId="19" lastPageNumber="212" pageId="18" pageNumber="211" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="B42B36B0875DB1071E0F5A21F6FEF3AD" blockId="18.[1365,2570,3123,3241]" box="[1366,2410,3123,3152]" pageId="18" pageNumber="211">
<emphasis id="86E0EAA2875DB1071E0F5A21FA65F3AD" bold="true" box="[1366,1521,3123,3152]" pageId="18" pageNumber="211">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="73944D33875DB1071EA45A21F85DF3AD" authority="Merriam, 1894" authorityName="Merriam" authorityYear="1894" box="[1533,1993,3123,3152]" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Perognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="18" pageNumber="211" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="baileyi">Perognathus baileyi Merriam, 1894</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation id="04FC3CED875DB1071C835A21F6FEF3AD" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3802894304" box="[2010,2410,3123,3152]" pageId="18" pageNumber="211">Magdalena, Sonora, Mexico.</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B42B36B0875DB1061E0E5A44FBF8FDD4" blockId="18.[1365,2570,3123,3241]" lastBlockId="19.[813,1409,284,712]" lastPageId="19" lastPageNumber="212" pageId="18" pageNumber="211">
Based on detailed sequencing of nDNA and mtDNA genes, 
<taxonomicName id="73944D33875DB10713FC5A44F68CF38A" authorityName="Merriam" authorityYear="1894" box="[2213,2328,3158,3191]" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Perognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="18" pageNumber="219" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="baileyi">C. baileyi</taxonomicName>
is a close relative of 
<taxonomicName id="73944D33875DB1071EDB5A6CF98AF362" baseAuthorityName="Elliot" baseAuthorityYear="1903" box="[1410,1566,3198,3231]" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Chaetodipus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="18" pageNumber="212" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rudinoris">C. rudinoris</taxonomicName>
(formerly considered conspecific), and the two species make up one of the three “ancient” clades of coarse-haired pocket mice. 
<taxonomicName id="73944D33875CB1061F3A5756FA15FE98" baseAuthorityName="Elliot" baseAuthorityYear="1903" box="[1123,1409,324,357]" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Chaetodipus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="19" pageNumber="212" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rudinoris">Chaetodipus rudinoris</taxonomicName>
has a chromosomal complement with a higher FN (66), lacks any supernumerary chromosomes, and is differentiated based on allozymes and mtDNA sequence. Two subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="E0EB6638875DB1071B045B10F8EBF270" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6611356" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6611356" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6611356/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="211" startId="18.[93,123,3330,3351]" targetBox="[11,2732,14,3643]" targetPageId="17">
<paragraph id="B42B36B0875DB1071B045B10F8EBF270" blockId="18.[92,2529,3330,3475]" pageId="18" pageNumber="211">
